-- Egypt's regulator approves Beltone-Sawiris bid for EFG Hermes stake
-- By Ehab Farouk
-- Wed Jun 18, 2014 04:32AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, June 18 (Reuters) - Egypt's financial regulator has approved a $257 billion joint bid by Beltone <BTFH.CA> and billionaire Naguib Sawiris for a 20 percent stake in EFG Hermes <HRHO.CA>, the head of the Egyptian Financial Supervisory Authority, Sharif Samy, said on Wednesday.

